columns.name: QUOTE_GID
columns.description: The GID for the quote.

columns.name: QUOTE_XID
columns.description: The XID for the quote.

columns.name: REQUEST_DATE
columns.description: The date that you received the request for the quote from the customer. If you leave this field blank, it defaults to the date that the quote is created.

columns.name: ISSUE_DATE
columns.description: The date the quote was sent to the customer.

columns.name: EXPIRATION_DATE
columns.description: Identifies the last day the quote is valid.

columns.name: ORIGIN_LOCATION_TYPE
columns.description: Type of location for the source location - equivalent to location role. Examples would include: Port, Rail Ramp etc. This limits the location search to these specific types of locations. The default Location Type is Location Code for both the Origin and Destination.

columns.name: ORIGIN_LOCATION_GID
columns.description: The GID for the origin/source location.

columns.name: ORIGIN_ADDRESS_LINE1
columns.description: Origin location address line 1 value.

columns.name: ORIGIN_ADDRESS_LINE2
columns.description: Origin location address line 2 value.

columns.name: ORIGIN_ADDRESS_LINE3
columns.description: Origin location address line 3 value.

columns.name: ORIGIN_CITY
columns.description: Origin location city value.

columns.name: ORIGIN_PROVINCE
columns.description: Origin location province value.

columns.name: ORIGIN_COUNTRY_CODE3_GID
columns.description: Origin location country code value.

columns.name: ORIGIN_POSTAL_CODE
columns.description: Origin location postal code value.

columns.name: VIA_ORIGIN_LOCATION_GID
columns.description: If applicable, the GID for the origin via location.

columns.name: DESTINATION_LOCATION_TYPE
columns.description: Type of location for the destination location - equivalent to location role. Examples would include: Port, Rail Ramp etc. This limits the location search to these specific types of locations. The default Location Type is Location Code for both the Destination and Destination.

columns.name: DESTINATION_LOCATION_GID
columns.description: The GID for the destination location.

columns.name: DESTINATION_ADDRESS_LINE1
columns.description: Destination location address line 1 value.

columns.name: DESTINATION_ADDRESS_LINE2
columns.description: Destination location address line 2 value.

columns.name: DESTINATION_ADDRESS_LINE3
columns.description: Destination location address line 3 value.

columns.name: DESTINATION_CITY
columns.description: Destination location city value.

columns.name: DESTINATION_PROVINCE
columns.description: Destination location province value.

columns.name: DESTINATION_COUNTRY_CODE3_GID
columns.description: Destination Location country code value.

columns.name: DESTINATION_POSTAL_CODE
columns.description: Destination location postal code value.

columns.name: VIA_DESTINATION_LOCATION_GID
columns.description: Job consolidation type to be used when determining the NFRC rules that may apply to this quote rate inquiry.

columns.name: IS_HAZARDOUS
columns.description: Flag indicating if the quote is for a shipment that contains hazardous material.

columns.name: PERSPECTIVE
columns.description: Perspective - buy or sell side.

columns.name: QUOTE_OPTION
columns.description: Select Optimize, Equipment Groups, or Equipment Configuration. Optimize returns quotes that match the search criteria. This is the default setting. Equipment Groups limit the search to specific Equipment Groups. When you select this option, an Equipment Group field appears where you can enter or search for an Equipment Group. Use the Save button to enter multiple Equipment Groups. Equipment Configuration works like the Equipment Groups option, but it provides you with a field to enter the number of Equipment Groups you require.

columns.name: TRANSPORT_MODE_GID
columns.description: The GID for the transport mode to for the quote. Select the mode that you want the master leg of the shipment to be transported on. The values in this drop-down list match the Transport Modes defined in Power Data.

columns.name: SERVPROV_GID
columns.description: The GID for the service provider for the quote. Enter the service provider that you want to use for the master leg of the shipment. The values available in this field match what is defined in the Service Provider Manager.

columns.name: AVAILABLE_BY_DATE
columns.description: The date the freight will be available by if the shipment will not be available to ship until a certain date.

columns.name: DELIVER_BY_DATE
columns.description: The date the freight must be delivered by if the shipment must be delivered by a certain date.

columns.name: ORIGIN_SEARCH_VALUE
columns.description: Origin rate search value.

columns.name: DESTINATION_SEARCH_VALUE
columns.description: Destination rate search value.

columns.name: IS_CUSTOMER_RATES_ONLY
columns.description: Flag to limit search to customer specific rates only.

columns.name: CONSOLIDATION_TYPE_GID
columns.description: Job consolidation type to be used when determining the NFRC rules that may apply to this quote rate inquiry.

columns.name: INCO_TERM_GID
columns.description: The GID for the Incoterm for the shipment. This can limit the itineraries considered.

columns.name: DOMAIN_NAME
columns.description: Database domain where this data is stored.

columns.name: INSERT_USER
columns.description: The user ID of the data insert user.

columns.name: INSERT_DATE
columns.description: Date and time of data insert.

columns.name: UPDATE_USER
columns.description: The user ID of the data update user.

columns.name: UPDATE_DATE
columns.description: Date and time of the most recent data update.
